Thulani Gqirana, News24(File, Saps) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; An 80-year-old farmer is recovering in hospital after he and his 78-year-old wife were attacked on their Villiersdorp farm in the Western Cape on Wednesday, police said.The farmer, Danie du Toit, was robbed of five firearms, wine, a television set and jewellery after four unidentified males gained entry to his farm at around 01:00, police said.The man was tied up with electrical cords and assaulted with a rifle, while his wife, Martie, was tied up with shoelaces and covered with a blanket.The 78-year-old woman raised the alarm after she managed to loosen the laces.She called her son, a doctor who lives in the area, who ran to their rescue.The African National Congress in the Western Cape said the 80-year-old man was in hospital undergoing tests.The robbers broke the butt of a rifle on his head, the party said in a statement.Police spokesperson Captain FC van Wyk said it was not clear how the robbers managed to flee the scene. Police have opened a case of house robbery.No arrests have been made so far.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.